<item>
            <title>[LU-7563] print a console warning for inconsistent LNet ip2nets configurations</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7563</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an interface is explicity specified as well as a pattern, the interface matched using the IP pattern should be sanitized against the explicitly defined interface, or print a warning.  For example, &lt;tt&gt;tcp(eth0) 192.168.&amp;#42;.3&lt;/tt&gt; and there exists in the system &lt;tt&gt;eth0 == 192.158.19.3&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;eth1 == 192.168.3.3&lt;/tt&gt;, then configuration is inconsistent, because the pattern contradicts the interface specified.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A clear warning should be displayed if inconsistent configuration is encountered so that this doesn&apos;t cause problems in the future.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
